Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.00,0:00:12.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Your personal ancestry story begins
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.00,0:00:20.08,Default,,0,0,0,,with the shared story of our human ancestry.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.00,0:00:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You and your distant cousin, the chimpanzee,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.00,0:00:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,have a common ancestor.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.00,0:00:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,which lived about 6.5 million years ago.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:31.00,0:00:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We can learn about this common ancestor by
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.00,0:00:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,noting what makes us similar to chimps.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:40.00,0:00:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But many things also distinguish us from chimpanzees,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.00,0:00:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like our big brains, which enable abstract reasoning
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.00,0:00:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and the development of complex languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.00,0:00:55.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And our anatomy, adapted to up-right walking,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:57.00,0:01:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these human traits developed gradually over millions of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.00,0:01:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The fossil record reveals a long and eventful
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.00,0:01:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,parade of human ancestors.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.00,0:01:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,During some periods, several of our ancestors co-existed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.00,0:01:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Gradually, they became more efficient up-right walkers.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.00,0:01:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And later, developed skulls with larger brain cases
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.00,0:01:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,devoted more to thinking and less to chewing.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.00,0:01:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Our knowledge of the exact relationships between
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.00,0:01:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,these ancestors is incomplete.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:37.00,0:01:41.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And often, is revised, because of new fossil finds.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.00,0:01:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Some of them were our direct ancestors,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.00,0:01:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,some of them were distant cousins,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.50,0:01:53.16,Default,,0,0,0,,who became evolutionary dead ends.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.00,0:01:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But by 200,000 years ago, we're on firmer ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.00,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We find the bones of people in Africa,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:02.00,0:02:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who looked something like us,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.00,0:02:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not exactly like us, but close.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.00,0:02:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They built fires and flaked stone into spear heads, knifes, and scrapers.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.00,0:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They were physically strong,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.00,0:02:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and still depended on their muscles, not their technology
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.50,0:02:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for much of their survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.00,0:02:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, in addition to fossils,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.00,0:02:35.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we have genetics to help us find our prehistoric kin.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.00,0:02:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this, living today, inherited our DNA from this small group of ancient people in Africa.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.00,0:02:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Over time, they began to look more and more like us.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:49.00,0:02:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,And by 100,000 years ago, their skeletons weren't so different
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.00,0:03:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,from ours, but these early Homo sapiens shared the planet
Dialogue: 0,0:03:01.00,0:03:04.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with two of their distant cousins.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.00,0:03:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,By this time, as a result of previous migrations,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:08.00,0:03:15.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo erectus was living across Asia, and had been for 2 million years.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.00,0:03:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Homo erectus had a big brain, some made hand axes,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.00,0:03:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some do fires, and some may even have worn clothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.00,0:03:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,At the same time, Neanderthals lived across Europe, and western and
Dialogue: 0,0:03:31.00,0:03:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,central Asia. They had even bigger brains.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.00,0:03:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They made spears and stone tools, similar to those
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.00,0:03:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,found in Africa, and we suspect they had strong social relationships.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.00,0:03:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They cared for the sick, and infirm, and buried their dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.00,0:03:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Not so very different, culturally, from early Homo sapiens, it seems
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.00,0:04:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that our human anatomy developed before our complex human culture.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.00,0:04:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But things were about to change.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:10.00,0:04:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, we live in all climates, all over the world;
Dialogue: 0,0:04:14.00,0:04:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and are unique, in our dependence on our cultures for survival.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.00,0:04:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,How we got from there, to here,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.00,0:04:29.01,Default,,0,0,0,,forms the next chapters in our human story.
